CatDescriptText: Mary McLeod Bethune (1875-1955), the founder of the Daytona Normal and Industrial Institute for Negro Girls (Bethune Cookman College).  She was also Director of Negro Affairs in the National Youth Administration from 1936-1944, and appointed consultant on interracial affairs and understanding at the charter conference of the U.N. Founder of the National Council of Negro Women, and Vice-president of the NAACP.
TitMainTitle: Woman embracing Mary McLeod Bethune, surrounded by a group of women
